31 May (4 days ago)
		
to jpawluk
Hello John and Anna,

As per our conversation, I have tabled below various sized systems, their impact on your av quarterly bill and prices (which are
AFTER the govt rebates) and prices, giving both German and Chinese inverter options. I have based the calculations on an average
quarterly bill of $350 of which $70 ish is the supply/service charge, hence a rounded figure of $280 allowing for this:

System size with 250 watt panels 	 Average quarterly bill -excluding $60-70 supply charge 	Approx reduced bill with solar 	Discount Price with German inverter -ends 26 May 	Discount price with Chinese inverter -ends  26 May
1.5kW   6 panels 	$280 	$126 	$1,899 	$1,899
2 kW     8 	$280 	$63 	$2,999 	$2,699
2.5        10 	$280 	$0 	$4,999 	$4,299
3kW     12 	$280 	$63 credit 	$5,999 	$4,999
Above calculations based on Feed in Tariff rate of 33cents per kWh with AGL.

Please review the above in accordance with your budget and how much you wish to reduce your
current electricity bill. Also take a look at our website, and I'll wait to hear back from you on Saturday/Sunday if you'd like me to prioritise you
and save you $900!

Enjoy your trip away meanwhile.


Regards
Jenny
